Lizeka Tandwa, News24DA. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories East London - Nqaba Bhanga will head up the DA's Eastern Cape leadership.The announcement was made at the DA's provincial elective conference in East London on Saturday.Bhanga faced off against Veliswa Mvenya.Bhanga who was recruited by Nelson Mandela Bay Mayor Athol Trollip was considered the favourite among the party's provincial leadership. Bhanga joined the party when he left Cope in 2014. &nbsp; It is believed that Bhanga will help strengthen Trollip's power in the national elective congress which will be highly contested.&nbsp; His detractors have called him a "Mafikizolo" in the party.&nbsp; During his speech, Trollip told delegates that they should not underestimate a new comer.&nbsp; He said that he was once a new comer in the party and DA leader Mmusi Maimane was also once a new comer.&nbsp;The newly-elected DA Eastern Cape leadership also includes two deputy provincial leaders, Bobby Stevenson and Terence Fritz. The provincial chairperson is Andrew Whitfield and three deputy provincial chairpersons, Yusuf Cassim, Kobus Botha and Marshall von Buchenroder. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.